    dc:creator "Shen, Huei-Ping; Chang, Chih-Han; Chih, Wen-Jay" ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Two new earthworm species of the genus Drawida (Oligochaeta: Moniligastridae) from southwestern Taiwan" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1446837>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1446839> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1446837>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Drawida fenqihuensis sp. nov. Holotype (TESRI-O-H-52). A. Ventral view of spermathecal and male pore region (sp, spermathecal pore; p, penis). B. Dorsal view of right spermatheca (amp, ampulla; sa, spermathecal atrium), testis sac (ts), sperm duct (sd), and male atrium (ma). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1446837/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1446839>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Neighbor-joining tree of Drawida based on COI gene and Kimura’s two-parameter model, and rooted using Amynthas corticis. Author and year of species names as follows: Dr. beiganica Shen & Chang, 2015, Dr. dongyinica Shen & Chih, 2015, Dr. eda Blakemore, 2010, Dr. japonica (Michaelsen, 1892), Dr. companio Blakemore, 2014, Dr. koreana Kobayashi, 1938, Dr. iucn Blakemore, 2013, Dr. anchingiana Chen, 1933, Dr. hattamimizu Hatai, 1930, Dr. odaesan Blakemore, 2014, Dr. jeombongsan Blakemore, 2014, Dr. songae yeongdo Blakemore, 2013, and Dr. impertusa Stephenson, 1920. Specimens from this study are shown by their voucher numbers (Ali). Sequences retrieved from GenBank are labelled with GenBank accession numbers. Sequences acquired from Blakemore et al. (2014) are labelled with the original sample IDs. Type materials are indicated and preceded by the specific epithets (in parentheses). Sp1–sp5 refer to unknown species recognized in Blakemore et al. (2014). Numbers around nodes are bootstrap values above 50." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1446839/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

